AGI -&nbsp;"In Europe, at this moment, there are so many districts. The Italian one, and I believe that everyone should acknowledge it, manages to maintain a position of balance and full adherence to democratic values. Let me say that who invented our half-year-old center had seen us long ago... >Today we live a very difficult historical phase and the role of Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni is quite complex: I'm convinced you deserve esteem and respect for what you're doing." Said Marina&nbsp;Berlusconi&nbsp; in an interview published by "Il Foglio".
&nbsp;
"Unfortunately - adds the president of Fininvest and the Mondadori group - the situation appears very different in other countries where the most radical movements are strengthening: in some cases even dictate the agenda of the most moderate forces. Europe must wake up. >Too often membership of the Union is still lived as a cession of sovereignty, as if more Europe meant less Italy, less Germany, less France... It is enough to see those movements which on the one hand proclaim that they want to make Europe great and on the other preach the motto of less Europe and more sovereignty. But exactly the opposite is true, because - it emphasizes - true sovereignty is able to respond to the needs of citizens and there can be no sovereignty in solitude, today less than ever. I am thinking of the common defence, the common foreign policy, the common debt, the single market for capital: all cases where union is strength." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
In the interview given to the director of "Il Foglio", Claudio Cerasa, Marina Berlusconi has also returned to talk about issues related to the sphere of rights, from gay marriages to surrogacy, from the end of life to citizenship for those born in Italy. "I'm in favour of gay marriages. Look if there's someone who values the family, well that's me. >Having a united and solid family has always been the main goal of my life. That's why I'm convinced that the family can't be stuck in standard patterns and models, but everyone has the right to create their own together with the person they love."

<div </div

"Other speech - the president of the Mondadori Group remarks - is that of surrogacy, on which I find myself opposed:> something intimate and profound as motherhood cannot turn into a trade of the female body. As far as assisted suicide is concerned, I think that those suffering from an incurable and painful disease must have the right to end their existence with dignity, > of course, on the basis of a decision taken in total freedom and awareness. I last held the topic of citizenship for those born in Italy because on this topic I think it is very gradual: too drastic and ideological positions only generate excesses in the opposite direction. It takes small steps forward, with the aim of a reasonable integration, without claiming to change the world in the space of one night, otherwise pendulum syndrome would strike again", concludes Marina Berlusconi.

